description: A list of information about signal decoders specified in a decoder manifest.

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: The name of the decoder manifest to list information about.

parameters.name: nextToken
parameters.description: A pagination token for the next set of results. If the results of a search are large, only a portion of the results are returned, and a nextToken pagination token is returned in the response. To retrieve the next set of results, reissue the search request and include the returned token. When all results have been returned, the response does not contain a pagination token value.

nested_items.name: signalDecoders
nested_items.description: Information about a list of signals to decode.

nested_items.name: fullyQualifiedName
nested_items.description: The fully qualified name of a signal decoder as defined in a vehicle model.

nested_items.name: type
nested_items.description: The network protocol for the vehicle. For example, CAN_SIGNAL specifies a protocol that defines how data is communicated between electronic control units (ECUs). OBD_SIGNAL specifies a protocol that defines how self-diagnostic data is communicated between ECUs.

nested_items.name: interfaceId
nested_items.description: The ID of a network interface that specifies what network protocol a vehicle follows.

nested_items.name: canSignal
nested_items.description: Information about signal decoder using the Controller Area Network (CAN) protocol.

nested_items.name: messageId
nested_items.description: The ID of the message.

nested_items.name: isBigEndian
nested_items.description: Whether the byte ordering of a CAN message is big-endian.

nested_items.name: isSigned
nested_items.description: Determines whether the message is signed ( true) or not ( false). If it's signed, the message can represent both positive and negative numbers. The isSigned parameter only applies to the INTEGER raw signal type, and it doesn't affect the FLOATING_POINT raw signal type.

nested_items.name: startBit
nested_items.description: Indicates the beginning of the CAN signal. This should always be the least significant bit (LSB).

nested_items.name: offset
nested_items.description: The offset used to calculate the signal value. Combined with factor, the calculation is value = raw_value * factor + offset.

nested_items.name: factor
nested_items.description: A multiplier used to decode the CAN message.

nested_items.name: length
nested_items.description: How many bytes of data are in the message.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: The name of the signal.

nested_items.name: signalValueType
nested_items.description: The value type of the signal. The default value is INTEGER.

nested_items.name: obdSignal
nested_items.description: Information about signal decoder using the on-board diagnostic (OBD) II protocol.

nested_items.name: pidResponseLength
nested_items.description: The length of the requested data.

nested_items.name: serviceMode
nested_items.description: The mode of operation (diagnostic service) in a message.

nested_items.name: pid
nested_items.description: The diagnostic code used to request data from a vehicle for this signal.

nested_items.name: scaling
nested_items.description: A multiplier used to decode the message.

nested_items.name: offset
nested_items.description: The offset used to calculate the signal value. Combined with scaling, the calculation is value = raw_value * scaling + offset.

nested_items.name: startByte
nested_items.description: Indicates the beginning of the message.

nested_items.name: byteLength
nested_items.description: The length of a message.

nested_items.name: bitRightShift
nested_items.description: The number of positions to shift bits in the message.

nested_items.name: bitMaskLength
nested_items.description: The number of bits to mask in a message.

nested_items.name: isSigned
nested_items.description: Determines whether the message is signed ( true) or not ( false). If it's signed, the message can represent both positive and negative numbers. The isSigned parameter only applies to the INTEGER raw signal type, and it doesn't affect the FLOATING_POINT raw signal type. The default value is false.

nested_items.name: signalValueType
nested_items.description: The value type of the signal. The default value is INTEGER.

nested_items.name: messageSignal
nested_items.description: The decoding information for a specific message which supports higher order data types.

nested_items.name: topicName
nested_items.description: The topic name for the message signal. It corresponds to topics in ROS 2.

nested_items.name: structuredMessage
nested_items.description: The structured message for the message signal. It can be defined with either a primitiveMessageDefinition, structuredMessageListDefinition, or structuredMessageDefinition recursively.

nested_items.name: primitiveMessageDefinition
nested_items.description: Represents a primitive type node of the complex data structure.

nested_items.name: ros2PrimitiveMessageDefinition
nested_items.description: Information about a PrimitiveMessage using a ROS 2 compliant primitive type message of the complex data structure.

nested_items.name: primitiveType
nested_items.description: The primitive type (integer, floating point, boolean, etc.) for the ROS 2 primitive message definition.

nested_items.name: offset
nested_items.description: The offset used to calculate the signal value. Combined with scaling, the calculation is value = raw_value * scaling + offset.

nested_items.name: scaling
nested_items.description: A multiplier used to decode the message.

nested_items.name: upperBound
nested_items.description: An optional attribute specifying the upper bound for STRING and WSTRING.

nested_items.name: structuredMessageListDefinition
nested_items.description: Represents a list type node of the complex data structure.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: The name of the structured message list definition.

nested_items.name: memberType
nested_items.description: The member type of the structured message list definition.

nested_items.name: listType
nested_items.description: The type of list of the structured message list definition.

nested_items.name: capacity
nested_items.description: The capacity of the structured message list definition when the list type is FIXED_CAPACITY or DYNAMIC_BOUNDED_CAPACITY.

nested_items.name: structuredMessageDefinition
nested_items.description: Represents a struct type node of the complex data structure.

nested_items.name: fieldName
nested_items.description: The field name of the structured message. It determines how a data value is referenced in the target language.

nested_items.name: customDecodingSignal
nested_items.description: Information about a custom signal decoder.

nested_items.name: id
nested_items.description: The ID of the signal.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: The token to retrieve the next set of results, or null if there are no more results.
